citation.case_name: St. Peter's Parish v. Urban Authority

html:
359 U.S. 435

79 S.Ct. 940

3 L.Ed.2d 931

ST. PETER'S ROMAN CATHOLIC PARISH
v.
URBAN REDEVELOPMENT AUTHORITY OF PITTSBURGH et al.

No. 749.

Supreme Court of the United States

May 4, 1959

Mr. Louis C. Glasso, for appellant.

Messrs. Theodore L. Hazlett, Jr. and R. J. Hopkins, for appellees.

PER CURIAM.

1

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed. Treating the papers whereon the appeal was taken as a petition for writ of certiorari, certiorari is denied.
